                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.52.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-14T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">June</hi> 14, 1912—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A request has been received for American protection for the Esperanza San Miguel
                    Sugar Mills, owned by the Spanish firm Marimon Bosch Co., Santiago. You may
                    bring this and similar cases informally and unofficially to the attention of the
                    Foreign Office, saying that the matter is of course not one primarily for the
                    cognizance of this Government, yet its friendship for and interest in Cuba’s
                    ultimate welfare prompts it to bring the case to the attention of the Cuban
                    Government, which it is hoped will take the measures necessary to obviate the
                    possibility of future embarrassment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
